attributes.additional_details:
The next PM must be someone:
i) who is in good standing in the community in general […]; 
ii) whose past conduct would not reasonably be regarded as creating a potential risk to the security of the UK;
iii) whose past conduct would not (had he or she been in public office at the relevant time) have constituted a material breach of the Seven Principles; and
iv) of whom there is a reasonable expectation that he or she will comply in full with the Ministerial Code and the Seven Principles.
